## 8. Active Alerts in PagerDuty

| Alert Name | Severity | What It Covers | Notes / Explanation |
|---|---|---|---|
| DiskRunsOutOfSpaceIn3Days | 🟠 Warning | Disk space depletion projection | Smart mathematical prediction guessing the disk will fill up in 72 hours. |
| DiskRunsOutOfSpace | 🔴 Critical | Disk usage > 80% | The drive is dangerously full right now. Performance issues are imminent. |
| RequestErrorsToAPI | 🟠 Warning | High HTTP error rate | The system detected more than 50 failed web requests within 5 minutes. |
| RPCErrors | 🟠 Warning | Internal network errors | Failure in internal service-to-service connection, dial, or handshakes. |
| ConcurrentFlushesHitTheLimit | 🟠 Warning | High flush activity | Too much data is being written to disk at once, overloading the storage CPU. |
| RowsRejectedOnIngestion | 🟠 Warning | Data ingestion issues | The database is throwing away incoming rows due to badly formatted data. |
| TooHighChurnRate | 🟠 Warning | New metrics creation rate | New tracking data points are being created too fast, hurting database performance. |
| TooHighChurnRate24h | 🟠 Warning | High churn over 24 hours | Continuous creation of too many new data series over a full day. |
| TooHighSlowInsertsRate | 🟠 Warning | Slow inserts rate > 5% | Over 5% of database writes are slow. Indicates a RAM shortage or database overload. |
| ProcessNearFDLimits | 🔴 Critical | File descriptor exhaustion | The application has opened too many files/sockets and will crash soon. |
| LabelsLimitExceededOnIngestion | 🟠 Warning | Label limit exceeded | Bad configurations or client data models are sending too many labels. |
| VminsertVmstorageConnectionIsSaturated | 🟠 Warning | Data component bottleneck | The connection between data-entry and data-storage is choked. Needs scaling. |
| PodNotReady | 🔴 Critical | Application is down | An application container has been broken, stuck, or offline for over 5 minutes. |

