## 9. Recommended Additions to PagerDuty Alerts
These are suggested metric configurations to add to our monitoring rules to improve coverage across infrastructure layers.
## Storage

* PVC usage > 80% (🔴 Critical): High risk of application storage crashing.
* Disk I/O latency (🟠 Warning): Disks are responding slowly, which degrades overall system performance.
* Fragmentation / reclaim space warnings (🟠 Warning): The disk is storing data inefficiently and needs space cleanup.

## Node Health

* CPU usage > 85% sustained (🔴 Critical): Server processors are working too hard and creating a bottleneck.
* Memory pressure over time (🟠/🔴 Mixed): Servers are running low on RAM. Severity changes depending on how fast memory disappears.
* Node unreachable (🔴 Critical): A physical server host has gone completely offline. Requires immediate investigation.

## Database

* Connection failures (🟠 Warning): Applications are struggling to log into the database. Possible database downtime.
* Transaction lock contention (🟠 Warning): Multiple database queries are fighting over the same data row, causing slow performance.
* Query timeout rates (🟠 Warning): Queries are taking too long to finish, directly slowing down the user experience.

## Network

* DNS resolution failures (🟠 Warning): Internal services cannot look up names or find each other. Service discovery is broken.
* Service endpoint unreachable (🔴 Critical): Core service web addresses are returning errors, impacting immediate availability.

## Airflow

* DAG failures count (🟠 Warning): Data processing workflows are failing to finish successfully.
* Scheduler offline (🔴 Critical): The engine that schedules data jobs is dead. No automatic workflows will run.
* Worker crash (🔴 Critical): The worker nodes executing data tasks have crashed. Task execution failure.

## Logging

* Fluent Bit ingestion errors (🟠 Warning): Log collection agents are hitting errors. Some logs might be missing.
* Dropped logs (🟠 Warning): The logging engine cannot keep up with traffic and is throwing data away, causing incomplete observability.
* Loki ingestion failures (🔴 Critical): The central logging system storage is completely broken.

## Queue Monitoring

* ASUPProcessorQueueStalled (🔴 Critical): Data processing queue depth has piled up to more than 5,000 items and has shown zero progress for 15 minutes.

------------------------------
## 10. Notes

* Include Dashboards: Always paste relevant Grafana data metrics links directly into PagerDuty timeline comments so teammates can see the graphs immediately.
* Tune Regularly: Review metric numbers every month to stop false alarms (alert fatigue).
* Smart Grouping: Ensure PagerDuty groups notifications by service type (e.g., Database alerts grouped together, Network alerts grouped together) to keep notifications organized.
* Keep Learning: Ensure new system outage takeaways are written directly back into this playbook document.

