## Part 1: Prometheus Alertmanager Rules (YAML)
These configuration files tell Prometheus exactly when to look for a problem and pass it to PagerDuty.
## 1. Prometheus Rule for PodNotReady

apiVersion: ://coreos.comkind: PrometheusRulemetadata:
  name: pod-not-ready-alert
  namespace: monitoringspec:
  groups:
  - name: application-alerts
    rules:
    - alert: PodNotReady
      # This checks if a pod is healthy. 0 means it is broken or down.
      expr: kube_pod_status_ready{condition="true"} == 0
      # The pod must be broken for 5 continuous minutes before triggering the alarm.
      for: 5m
      labels:
        severity: critical
      annotations:
        summary: "Application pod {{ $labels.pod }} is down"
        description: "The pod {{ $labels.pod }} in namespace {{ $labels.namespace }} has been offline for more than 5 minutes."

## 2. Prometheus Rule for PVCUsageTooHigh (Storage Alert)

apiVersion: ://coreos.comkind: PrometheusRulemetadata:
  name: storage-alerts
  namespace: monitoringspec:
  groups:
  - name: disk-alerts
    rules:
    - alert: PVCUsageTooHigh
      # This divides used space by total space. If it is more than 0.80 (80%), it alerts.
      expr: (kubelet_volume_stats_used_bytes / kubelet_volume_stats_capacity_bytes) > 0.80
      for: 10m
      labels:
        severity: critical
      annotations:
        summary: "Storage disk {{ $labels.persistentvolumeclaim }} is nearly full"
        description: "Disk usage is over 80% for volume {{ $labels.persistentvolumeclaim }}."

