## Part 2: Simple Post-Incident Review Template (Retrospective)
Fill out this template within 48 hours after a major problem is fixed. It helps the team learn from mistakes.

# Post-Incident Review (PIR)## 1. Summary (What happened?)* **Incident Name**: [Example: Production Database Outage]
* **Date of Incident**: [YYYY-MM-DD]
* **Total Downtime**: [Example: 45 minutes]
* **Who was affected?**: [Example: Customers could not log into their profiles]
## 2. Timeline (When did things happen?)* **14:00** - The database ran out of memory. The server crashed.* **14:05** - PagerDuty sent a 🔴 Critical alert to the primary on-call engineer.* **14:10** - The primary engineer acknowledged the alert and started checking logs.* **14:30** - The engineer restarted the service and scaled up the server RAM.* **14:45** - The website was fully working again. The incident was closed.
## 3. Root Cause Analysis (Why did it happen?)* Why did the website stop working? Because the database crashed.* Why did the database crash? Because it ran out of RAM memory.* Why did it run out of RAM memory? Because a new software update caused a slow query that trapped data loops.
